main event: A single unidentified object with controlled flight was observed in the Atlantic Ocean on May 14, 1961.
interesting points: The object was too high to note its shape, size, or type of propulsion.
The object had neither a rocket nor meteor-like tail.
The object first headed north, then stopped, made an easy turn, and headed south before disappearing over the horizon.
The period of observation was about 5 minutes.
The object was as bright as a first-magnitude star.
sighted object: A single unidentified object with controlled flight
